{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "matrix": "code_ui_remote_model_generation",
  "defaults": {
    "provider": {
      "mode": "model_from_env_file",
      "envFile": ".env.test",
      "providerEnv": "LIBRA_CODE_TEST_PROVIDER",
      "modelEnv": "LIBRA_CODE_TEST_MODEL",
      "required": true
    },
    "options": {
      "control": "write",
      "browserControl": "off",
      "context": "dev",
      "approvalPolicy": "never",
      "timeoutMs": 120000
    }
  },
  "cases": [
    {
      "name": "model_generation_code_service_creates_tested_rust_file",
      "priority": "P0",
      "steps": [
        {
          "name": "attach automation",
          "op": "attach",
          "kind": "automation",
          "clientId": "model-generation-rust-file",
          "auth": "valid_control",
          "expect": {
            "status": 200,
            "saveToken": "current"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "call Code service with live model generation prompt",
          "op": "submitAndWaitIdle",
          "text": "/run Create a complete Rust source file named generated_model_greeting.rs. Use apply_patch to add the file. The file must define `pub fn greeting(name: &str) -> String` returning `hello, {name}` and include self-contained unit tests proving greeting(\"libra\") == \"hello, libra\". After the patch is applied, reply with exactly: Generated generated_model_greeting.rs.",
          "token": "current",
          "auth": "valid_control",
          "timeoutMs": 120000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 200,
            "assertions": [
              "snapshot_status_idle",
              "transcript_contains:Generated generated_model_greeting.rs"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "generated model file exists",
          "op": "readRepoFile",
          "path": "generated_model_greeting.rs",
          "expect": {
            "assertions": [
              "file_contains:pub fn greeting",
              "file_contains:greeting(\"libra\")",
              "file_contains:hello, {name}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "generated model code tests pass",
          "op": "runRepoCommand",
          "command": [
            "sh",
            "-c",
            "rustc --test generated_model_greeting.rs -o generated_model_greeting_test && ./generated_model_greeting_test"
          ],
          "timeoutMs": 20000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 0,
            "assertions": [
              "stdout_or_stderr_contains:test result: ok"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "model_generation_linked_cargo_cli_project_passes_quality_gates",
      "priority": "P0",
      "steps": [
        {
          "name": "attach automation",
          "op": "attach",
          "kind": "automation",
          "clientId": "model-generation-linked-cli",
          "auth": "valid_control",
          "expect": {
            "status": 200,
            "saveToken": "current"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "call Code service with linked Cargo CLI project prompt",
          "op": "submitAndWaitIdle",
          "text": "/run Execute this end-to-end test case in the current workspace. 1. Initialize a Rust project named `linked` by using the cargo command and disable Version Control System support with `cargo new linked --vcs none`. 2. Implement a clap-based CLI with exactly three subcommands: `code`, `cloud`, and `backup`; each command must print only its command name followed by a newline. 3. Make `cargo fmt --all --check` pass. 4. Make `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass. 5. Add test code under `linked/tests/` so `cargo test --all` passes and verifies the subcommands plus empty config behavior. 6. Implement config loading from the user's `$HOME` directory by reading `$HOME/.linked/config`; an empty config file must be valid. 7. Use Rust edition 2024. 8. Update the workspace `.libraignore` to include Rust build output directories, especially `target/`. When finished, reply with exactly: Generated linked Cargo CLI project.",
          "token": "current",
          "auth": "valid_control",
          "timeoutMs": 180000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 200,
            "assertions": [
              "snapshot_status_idle",
              "transcript_contains:Generated linked Cargo CLI project"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cargo project metadata is correct",
          "op": "readRepoFile",
          "path": "linked/Cargo.toml",
          "expect": {
            "assertions": [
              "file_contains:name = \"linked\"",
              "file_contains:edition = \"2024\"",
              "file_contains:clap"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "CLI implementation includes commands and home config path",
          "op": "readRepoFile",
          "path": "linked/src/main.rs",
          "expect": {
            "assertions": [
              "file_contains_any:Subcommand|subcommand",
              "file_contains:code",
              "file_contains:cloud",
              "file_contains:backup",
              "file_contains:.linked",
              "file_contains:config"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "integration tests cover cli and config behavior",
          "op": "readRepoFile",
          "path": "linked/tests/cli.rs",
          "expect": {
            "assertions": [
              "file_contains:#[test]",
              "file_contains:code",
              "file_contains:cloud",
              "file_contains:backup",
              "file_contains:.linked",
              "file_contains:config"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "workspace libraignore ignores Rust build output",
          "op": "readRepoFile",
          "path": ".libraignore",
          "expect": {
            "assertions": [
              "file_contains:target/"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "cargo project has no nested VCS metadata",
          "op": "repoFileAbsent",
          "path": "linked/.git"
        },
        {
          "name": "cargo fmt check passes",
          "op": "runRepoCommand",
          "command": [
            "sh",
            "-c",
            "cd linked && cargo fmt --all --check"
          ],
          "timeoutMs": 30000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "cargo clippy strict check passes",
          "op": "runRepoCommand",
          "command": [
            "sh",
            "-c",
            "cd linked && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings"
          ],
          "timeoutMs": 120000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "cargo tests pass",
          "op": "runRepoCommand",
          "command": [
            "sh",
            "-c",
            "cd linked && cargo test --all"
          ],
          "timeoutMs": 120000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "commands read empty home config and print exact names",
          "op": "runRepoCommand",
          "command": [
            "sh",
            "-c",
            "mkdir -p test-home/.linked && : > test-home/.linked/config && export HOME=\"$(pwd)/test-home\" && cd linked && test \"$(cargo run --quiet -- code)\" = code && test \"$(cargo run --quiet -- cloud)\" = cloud && test \"$(cargo run --quiet -- backup)\" = backup && test ! -s ../test-home/.linked/config"
          ],
          "timeoutMs": 120000,
          "expect": {
            "status": 0
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
